# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Uni_Vision — Primary OCR Modelfile (Gemma 4 E2B Q4_K_M — Multimodal)
#
# This Modelfile creates a quantised, context-clamped variant of
# Gemma 4 E2B optimised for visual encoding and OCR extraction
# on an 8 GiB VRAM budget (RTX 4070).
#
# Gemma 4 E2B is MULTIMODAL (Text + Image + Audio):
#   - 5.1B total params, 2.3B effective (MoE)
#   - Vision encoder ~150M params, variable resolution
#   - 128K context window (clamped to 4096 for VRAM)
#   - Q4_K_M quantization, 7.2 GB on disk
#
# VRAM Budget:
#   Region A (weights):  ~5000 MB (7.2 GB disk, fits entirely on GPU)
#   Region B (KV cache):   256 MB (4096 token context)
#   Region D (system):     512 MB (CUDA runtime + OS)
#   Total:               ~5768 MB / 8192 MB ceiling (2424 MB headroom)
#
# Build:
#   ollama create uni-vision-ocr -f config/ollama/Modelfile.ocr
#
# Run validation:
#   ollama show uni-vision-ocr --modelfile
#   ollama run uni-vision-ocr "test"
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

FROM gemma4:e2b

# ── Quantization & Memory Parameters ─────────────────────────────
# Q4_K_M provides 4-bit mixed quantisation.
# Gemma 4 E2B at 7.2 GB fits entirely on GPU — no CPU offload.
# num_ctx = 4096 (reduced from 128K for VRAM headroom).
# num_predict = 256 limits generation length for OCR output.

PARAMETER num_ctx 4096
PARAMETER num_predict 256
PARAMETER temperature 1.0
PARAMETER top_p 0.95
PARAMETER top_k 64
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1
PARAMETER repeat_last_n 128
PARAMETER num_keep 4
PARAMETER seed 42
PARAMETER stop </result>
PARAMETER stop </adjudication>
PARAMETER stop <end_of_turn>

# Penalise common LLM verbiage that is never valid OCR output
PARAMETER penalize_newline true
PARAMETER num_thread 4

# ── Low-level GGML parameters ────────────────────────────────────
# num_batch: tokens processed in parallel per forward pass.
#   256 is conservative for dual-model VRAM swapping.
# num_gpu: layers offloaded to GPU.
#   -1 = all layers (Gemma 4 E2B Q4_K_M fits entirely at 7.2 GB).

PARAMETER num_batch 256
PARAMETER num_gpu -1
PARAMETER main_gpu 0

# ── System Prompt (baked into the model) ──────────────────────────
# The SYSTEM block is prepended to every conversation and cannot
# be overridden by user messages.  This forces structured XML
# output without conversational filler.

SYSTEM """You are a precision OCR and text extraction engine for visual detection systems.
You will receive a cropped image region containing text, labels, identifiers, or markings.
Extract the text exactly as it appears in the image.

OUTPUT FORMAT — respond with ONLY a single <result> XML block:
<result>
  <detected_text>EXTRACTED_TEXT</detected_text>
  <confidence>0.00</confidence>
  <char_bboxes>x1,y1,x2,y2;x1,y1,x2,y2;...</char_bboxes>
  <reasoning>Brief analysis of character clarity</reasoning>
</result>

RULES:
1. detected_text: preserve the original casing and characters as they appear. Strip extraneous whitespace.
2. confidence: float 0.0–1.0 representing your certainty.
3. char_bboxes: semicolon-separated x1,y1,x2,y2 pixel coordinates per character. Output NONE if undetermined.
4. reasoning: one sentence only.
5. If unreadable: detected_text=UNREADABLE, confidence=0.0.
6. Never guess. Lower confidence on ambiguity.
7. NEVER produce conversational text, preamble, sign-off, or explanation outside the XML block.
8. Output the <result> block and absolutely nothing else."""

# ── Template Override ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Force Gemma 4's chat template to suppress any assistant preamble.

TEMPLATE """{{ if .System }}<start_of_turn>
{{ .System }}
<end_of_turn>
{{ end }}<start_of_turn>user
{{ .Prompt }}<end_of_turn>
<start_of_turn>model
"""
